oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Two photographs of Knox Newman and Pettis Graham Gordon
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two photographs of the same soldiers, Knox Newman and Pettis Graham Gordon, and a French madame. Gordon served in the 323rd Inf. Regt., 81st Div. and it is assumed that Newman did as well. Gordon returned to Rutherford County, Tennessee and eloped with Jessie Harrison [Gwjack 162].
